text.tspan: Prevalence of alcohol use disorders by age, World
Share of the population within particular age categories suffering from alcohol use disorders. Alcohol dependence is
defined by the International Classification of Diseases as the presence of three or more indicators of dependence for
at least a month within the previous year.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
